Oluwatenola Jermaine Womandi aka LordMaine may just be a 6-year-old kid but his profile is rising daily in the fashion industry with the help of his mother, Toyin Lawani. Lawani is a popular celebrity stylist and entrepreneur who has built a name for herself over the years. Recently, LordMaine became a brand ambassador for Croston Homes. He didn’t just get some money, he was also given land. The kid has modelled for several clothing brands and also represented brands such as Payporte. Besides modelling, the mother has helped him set up a clothing line – Elegant Kids. He has also launched a YouTube channel and trains kids on keeping fit and eating right.